  "boundaryRules": [
    "Console may call Fabric only through package boundary exports or published service APIs.",
    "Console may call Ledger only through package boundary exports or published service APIs.",
    "Implemented route means page + domain API client + server route + service boundary are all named, except static content may be API-free.",
    "Folded routes are current reachable URLs rendered by a parent page; they must be refreshable and guarded.",
    "External routes are current integration entry points and must name the external URL or integration boundary.",
    "Active route contract contains only current commercial truth; future, reserved, and prune candidates live in route backlog.",
    "Every enabled route has a stable route id used by menus, actions, and routeTo().",
    "Lab Owner routes expose business outcomes; Admin routes expose operator evidence and operations.",
    "Do not add compatibility routes for retired APIs; move active callers to the current route and delete the old route."
